    <p class="about_text">Connemara National Park in County Galway, covers 2,957 hectares of mountains, bogs, heaths, grasslands and wood landscapes. Some of the Park's mountains, such as Bencullagh, Benbaun, Benbrack and Muckanagh are part of the TwelveBens. The National Park was established and opened to the public in 1980 and is a must see attraction in Co.Galway.</p>
